 that what made the experience of these women unique was the dual confrontation with modernity itself and with Japan as a colonial power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSex rolezKoreaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenzKoreaxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093415340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520934153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520934153/original  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles